-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:138:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:141:            \"When using dynamic-access strategies, keep generated tests even when they do not improve \"\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:142:            \"dynamic-access coverage.\"\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:4:> [Dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:157:    \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:12:    \"\"\"Composite strategy that runs a primary workflow then improves dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:35:            self._print_message(\"no primary workflow configured, skipping to dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:46:                self._print_message(\"skipping dynamic-access coverage phase because primary workflow did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:52:        self._print_message(\"starting dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:61:            \"dynamic-access coverage phase completed with phase_ok={phase_ok}, iterations_added={iterations}\".format(\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:68:            self._print_message(\"keeping primary workflow result because dynamic-access coverage phase did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:20:    \"\"\"Bulk dynamic-access coverage strategy that shows the full report to the agent.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:22:    REQUIRED_PROMPTS = [\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\"]\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.