[thinking] **Considering class resources**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm wondering if classes could be seen as resources. In a native image, it seems that the classloader only includes resources from the classpath specifically for resource configuration. Maybe we could add resource-config to include MemoryUtil.class? However, it feels like dynamic class loading of bytecode in native images doesn't actually allow you to define classes. There’s a bit of complexity here, which makes me think more about how this all fits together.
[thinking] 
