[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class resources**\n\nI'm wondering if classes could be seen as resources. In a native image, it seems that the classloader only includes resources from the classpath specifically for resource configuration. Maybe we could add resource-config to include MemoryUtil.class? However, it feels like dynamic class loading of bytecode in native images doesn't actually allow you to define classes. There’s a bit of complexity here, which makes me think more about how this all fits together.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02c2857ea90408210169f56eed8b0881968e23cfba0bd31285\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9W77rrFf0oQWiuXGDu36ab5VofteRaMc_ryyJmrxcoOxFtVtSWgc3paoWnnblxEDcTLWn4kMF059LGQICDrUiZBhDFYhvCTYk_Q02UHm0JOadRB176IUXqRYGp0goBpzPubuoJtrL_Q1dUcZlChVnO9QuGYvrKStQs7993KJfY-2v41jJI7ZudyJKoYhdNrv1Q-a2J17uMnqi7Cw_IsAE9O81UBVQfkpOsxhgogMoWpAtT7H3qBqtJp9zQIyGis55ARfBiiWPUMd9AGUtqFCfw0n_37leD2m3MdEZmvSSSKpNSdN1NzXBWiT4ma2UIVEtF1dIHcejlYtS0ciVG9FOwyfoeXjBZgEFAwL8NugGKrgS1Voeo2d0a7NUNIlBWfC0lBxOx9JjTsb-jkhZXNhQM9swwLnOfFV3snsdEQAr7jGK6PV2-btZE0JZdM0D0AQjOxYAXnu5lJ0ek4v3lhrF3y1_vky8biew4nzzsBHygErYF0U_0jpHslTjKgvRm28AFtc05Ot16qcew__P-oJc-FsNxFrac1CiPDAJGSwg2CCzmXccfoJXFbRDXWepjkHGAIBqrdExe2EzPI6ePnch9hyvnC5MUbayUo0LoY6YennsIXaX6wfH6jQJSuaW-QI_r5cwuuBHyWcVJIxnJmIoT3bQB3urJT7KgCmkKDSg7sMf2ENsoCQJwwi91vCtF6qn_dFQeE3TutfKMHSOTcldsmjlm3tlEoLWjdMZSejUhbnhTb3gb6p8JzxHZAYUOWdgRf2QrG6Qu_1tMAJHeiKCsmljZf5qipSNDzZMxPPDh-BrGlaKd6FFuJWvvYxhKzQLuHMcDBZ5El52f47WTiT1kI52D3UnqQYWDaiX9QsDMjDZVK7s6f1cEkmRtfcrT9FrwLa1CHW0GmyLJ0Ej1SOlsafTxrgLvAkZox2L-r4TQ-cyulloO27ipy3hvrABvS07d5kZ4H4-77gfUEvxfMIVav0zqGD5mMlOQHRI-MjFijG9onLWyjT7qF0HW6y34bnTfUQ5k0keVVkFJ6IiZg00fKY5F6ti2-OtbH0COxLDh864BYq6YF-Nu6eSLPZSXhzrQ_BL_rV1J8TLONR5mruIyjGE4WLmv0m2IomsdO52kNwXxD6-RRt1IwS2HF3PAXd_ZyJ_KEj7MTPADTyXW828ng85c53CrOBAOve4C2R0mYLVga_zjmwlY1rYD2UHVBGpR5CP5pN61FJshxHByeZpDSvUx7ugk