[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering classpath issues**\n\nI'm thinking about how under Native Image, URLClassLoader dynamic loading isn't supported. There's a chance that locating the classpath might fail before an error occurs. I wonder if we should use a try block for the arrowMemoryCoreJarUrl. If it fails due to the missing classpath, should we really skip it? But then, this path seems like it would only improve coverage in the JVM agent, not necessarily for native test coverage. Interesting dilemma!\n\n**Considering naming conventions**\n\nI’m thinking about whether “directBufferWraps…” is a suitable name, especially if the buffer is null. I wonder if renaming it to “directBufferConstructorPathsAreExercised” might be more descriptive. On the other hand, maybe it’s not necessary to change it. I’m also pondering if it makes sense to run a test with this naming decision. There’s a lot to weigh here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02c2857ea90408210169f56f2ccfd88196be65f837fa841845\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9W88wT0e7YRE5rAIowdf2d-1r-vu-ioBMxAJ5feJA9iw5-cbsor1Ld9N9xPcfhLHCYOBE3Hpy7VsbHXy5YLiN86ZZAIDXkCrvZkhiB7FLLfHrt9BxpH30AAhCF_3BG6qWmpQNyakpuDDqJflgaqkOvFRHL7Ua8jSD2u8-PrScnmzxdB6PtNceMgY4FCpKTq5kRkviTZ-t-ajM65KiTYZHVxc-7Z7WSCw7p8mSgo2mF2N1blJoNClcw7CzWVV9ukU-RfqNHndn748_zqS4rvB8-IxL6Tgd1uZJy1vFG_B3xbWTj0YCBLEImrunyMLHBlBKEVDT-siEVlDJccqETS7GpwWXSXvohYcvxTsL-f6rwHuMqM3Lbu2xAqD7i87UkYMNaQXRrz15yU4sOQiqYMfgDaDJKzLUVfRliKTlrLb2WALRFI_7WB5sCmoF7lk1BJSAcASjDGoSO0Nwdwd3eaqK5o_WgNqap8pGcnDBsgfmMh4jdWQrd9D_JqxDSHrgXsJ9Y3MXIilBR7HgKZw80LErRrqwPlig4AlMmaAbDbO2OllR7KDp2iMk1SyKXJuTwfeTn_Sd8RbQpcLHe4AxeZdS9MgAIfAKbZaSamh4Ot5w_tRTPdYIPzVw4_TJMrQtAvrcRu4_Uvvpdco3nVy553cMl1mYs0mY51_7pHZr9oQf4fLBehbJhh2q5jwQfzZkyl6mga43Enobi-fREyd8CtFVADMRsXomIIvexBkXV3cch_CSM0JUbsHyz-WwpP-zbbZUPUMPhyARTcj2SMItrOmx4w4YWYBpUP5uHaXzzEwv39zAgnulWmRFUZeHV5w2OpWe7d_DGr0d4T7izrQ-LGBT